Margin

GwCnt

19 The demodulation margin (Margin) is an 8-bit unsigned integer in the range of 0..254 20 indicating the link margin in dB of the last successfully received LinkCheckReq command. 21 A value of ―0‖ means that the frame was received at the demodulation floor (0 dB or no 22 margin) while a value of ―20‖, for example, means that the frame reached the gateway 20 dB 23 above the demodulation floor. Value ―255‖ is reserved.

24 The gateway count (GwCnt) is the number of gateways that successfully received the last 25 LinkCheckReq command.

