5 Following the convention defined in the ―Physical layer‖ section of the Class A specification, 6 the ―Min data rate‖ subfield designates the lowest data rate allowed on this channel. For 7 example 0 designates DR0 / 125 kHz in the EU physical layer. Similarly ―Max data rate‖ 8 designates the highest data rate. For example in the EU spec, DrRange = 0x77 means that 9 only 50 kbps GFSK is allowed on a channel and DrRange = 0x50 means that DR0 / 125 kHz 10 to DR5 / 125 kHz are supported.

